1
00:00:20,845 --> 00:00:23,837
[Explosions In Distance]

2
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:32,479
[Incoming Shells Whistling]

3
00:01:04,488 --> 00:01:07,480
[Machine-gun Fire]

4
00:01:19,403 --> 00:01:22,372
[Panting]

5
00:01:27,845 --> 00:01:29,836
[Machine-gun Fire]

6
00:01:38,255 --> 00:01:41,247
[Droning]

7
00:01:54,972 --> 00:01:57,964
[Machine-gun Fire]

8
00:03:51,121 --> 00:03:54,113
[Machine-gun Fire]

9
00:03:57,461 --> 00:03:59,452
[Explosion]

10
00:04:22,686 --> 00:04:25,211
[Chattering]

11
00:04:29,893 --> 00:04:31,884
- Up! Up!
- Push!

12
00:04:34,064 --> 00:04:36,726
- Come on!
- Push!

13
00:04:55,185 --> 00:04:58,677
[Man] Move out of the way!
Clear the way!

14
00:05:03,794 --> 00:05:07,230
- [Shouting, Indistinct]
- [Neighing]

15
00:05:28,986 --> 00:05:31,113
[Man]
Move! Move!

16
00:05:35,292 --> 00:05:37,886
That was a full bottle,
Herr Leutnant.

17
00:05:39,663 --> 00:05:41,654
Yes!

18
00:05:55,145 --> 00:05:57,136
[Brakes Squeal]

19
00:06:39,289 --> 00:06:41,655
[Droning In Distance]

20
00:07:18,262 --> 00:07:20,526
[Klaxon Blaring]

21
00:07:29,439 --> 00:07:32,431
[Blaring Continues]

22
00:08:13,317 --> 00:08:16,286
[Loud Droning]

23
00:08:26,129 --> 00:08:29,621
- You've just met Willi von Klugermann!
- Yes!

24
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:32,464
- I see you've heard of him!
- Oh! Yes, I have!

25
00:08:32,536 --> 00:08:34,527
- [Man] Look at him!
- You must be the new...

26
00:08:34,605 --> 00:08:37,574
- He's tearing the wings off that plane!
- Let him celebrate, Ziegel!

27
00:08:37,641 --> 00:08:41,975
He shoots them down!
Your job is to keep him up there!

28
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:46,415
You must be
the new replacement... Stachel!

29
00:08:46,483 --> 00:08:48,474
Bruno Stachel,
Herr Oberleutnant.

30
00:08:48,552 --> 00:08:52,113
- Are you the adjutant?
- I fly a desk now!

31
00:08:52,189 --> 00:08:54,487
Anti-aircraft fire!

32
00:08:54,558 --> 00:08:58,050
Still, it could've got me
higher up, couldn't it?

33
00:08:58,128 --> 00:09:00,119
- Yes!
- [Chuckling]

34
00:09:00,197 --> 00:09:03,291
Wait here!
I'll tell the C! O! You've arrived!

35
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:06,359
And if I were you,
I'd button up that jacket!

36
00:09:22,552 --> 00:09:25,453
Ziegel! How soon
can you have us ready again?

37
00:09:25,522 --> 00:09:28,548
Depends on how many of the others
have been hit, Herr Hauptmann.

38
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:30,616
I wasn't the only one!

39
00:09:30,694 --> 00:09:33,720
I can't keep these barges flying forever!
I'm a mechanic, not a magician!

40
00:09:33,797 --> 00:09:36,925
No, you are a magician,
whether you like it or not!

41
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:40,458
- Only 11 back, Herr Hauptmann.
- Yes! Mueller went down!

42
00:09:40,537 --> 00:09:44,064
- He didn't last long!
- [Airplane Approaching Quickly]

43
00:09:47,210 --> 00:09:49,474
Fabian, how did we
come to lose him?

44
00:09:49,546 --> 00:09:51,912
I gave him the usual
instructions!!!

45
00:09:51,982 --> 00:09:53,973
But he wouldn't
stay with me!

46
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:56,042
Too, uh!!!
Too keen!

47
00:09:56,119 --> 00:09:58,883
- By the way, Scholte's replacement's here!
- [Boot Heels Click]

48
00:09:58,956 --> 00:10:01,891
Leutnant Bruno Stachel reporting
from 104 Training School.

49
00:10:01,959 --> 00:10:04,723
Your commanding officer...
Hauptmann Heidemann.

50
00:10:04,795 --> 00:10:07,286
Ah, yes! Stachel!
Come inside!

51
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:13,332
[Men Chattering, Laughing]

52
00:10:15,205 --> 00:10:17,605
Herr Hauptmann.

53
00:10:17,674 --> 00:10:20,165
- Stachel!
- Yes, sir!

54
00:10:21,445 --> 00:10:25,245
- [Boot Heels Click]
- Two years in the infantry!

55
00:10:25,315 --> 00:10:28,409
- Any rank?
- Corporal, Herr Hauptmann.

56
00:10:28,485 --> 00:10:31,545
What made you transfer
to the Air Corps?

57
00:10:31,621 --> 00:10:33,612
To fly,
Herr Hauptmann.

58
00:10:34,958 --> 00:10:37,119
Are you a good flyer?

59
00:10:37,194 --> 00:10:41,255
I am!!!
Comfortable in the air!

60
00:10:41,331 --> 00:10:43,424
"Comfortable!"
Are you?

61
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,832
- Interesting!
- [Man] Willi!

62
00:10:45,902 --> 00:10:47,893
- [Excited Chatter]
- Willi!

63
00:10:47,971 --> 00:10:50,371
[Men Laughing]

64
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,876
Very pretty flying!

65
00:10:53,944 --> 00:10:56,435
I wish you would stop it!
You'll live longer!

66
00:10:56,513 --> 00:10:59,311
[Chattering,
Laughing Continue]

67
00:11:00,951 --> 00:11:03,283
Sorry about that!

68
00:11:03,353 --> 00:11:06,220
I see you are
from Wiesbaden!

69
00:11:06,289 --> 00:11:08,780
I've done some hunting
around there!

70
00:11:10,460 --> 00:11:13,224
- Who are your people?
- Herr Hauptmann?

71
00:11:15,832 --> 00:11:17,959
I want to know something
of your background!

72
00:11:18,035 --> 00:11:21,129
What does
your father do?

73
00:11:26,243 --> 00:11:28,734
He works in a small hotel,
Herr Hauptmann.

74
00:11:30,313 --> 00:11:33,305
- Five bedrooms!
- [Scoffing Sighs]

75
00:11:36,019 --> 00:11:39,182
Corporal, see the new officer's bags
are taken up to the mess!

76
00:11:39,256 --> 00:11:42,521
- Herr Hauptmann.
- Come into my office, Stachel!

77
00:11:42,592 --> 00:11:45,356
[Chattering]

78
00:11:46,930 --> 00:11:48,921
Close the door,
please!

79
00:11:53,770 --> 00:11:57,570
I'm sorry if it bothers you
about what your father does!

80
00:11:57,641 --> 00:12:00,132
It doesn't bother me,
Herr Hauptmann.

81
00:12:04,681 --> 00:12:07,172
Then why are you
so touchy about it?

82
00:12:09,252 --> 00:12:13,746
Well, you're an officer now! Your
social problems are no concern of ours!

83
00:12:15,492 --> 00:12:17,483
Take a look at the map, Stachel!

84
00:12:21,098 --> 00:12:25,728
Our operating area is between Arras
and Saint-Quentin!

85
00:12:27,671 --> 00:12:32,040
The British also operate the area,
as you'll find out!

86
00:12:39,216 --> 00:12:42,413
Uh, what did you
train on?

87
00:12:42,486 --> 00:12:46,320
The usual machine, Herr Hauptmann...
an out-of-date Pfalz!

88
00:12:46,389 --> 00:12:51,156
- That's what you'll fly here!
- But, at flying school, they told us...

89
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:53,924
"Flying school!"
[Laughing]

90
00:12:53,997 --> 00:12:56,397
At flying school,
they'll tell you anything!

91
00:12:56,466 --> 00:13:00,129
Up-to-date machines
go to experienced pilots!

92
00:13:00,203 --> 00:13:02,637
Those are in short supply!

93
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,767
It's a cruel world,
Stachel, huh?

94
00:13:05,842 --> 00:13:07,833
Yes, Herr Hauptmann.

95
00:13:07,911 --> 00:13:13,076
Welcome to the squadron! The truck will
take you to the mess with the others!

96
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:15,880
[Boot Heels Click]

97
00:13:15,952 --> 00:13:17,943
And, Stachel!

98
00:13:20,190 --> 00:13:22,181
Let's hope
you get to like us!

99
00:13:29,199 --> 00:13:32,362
Of course, he could've
been lying about the five bedrooms!

100
00:13:32,435 --> 00:13:34,403
[Chuckling] His father
was probably only a waiter!

101
00:13:34,471 --> 00:13:36,939
- Just another snob, in fact.
- [Chattering]

102
00:13:37,007 --> 00:13:39,237
Willi, there's something
I haven't told you!

103
00:13:39,309 --> 00:13:41,539
I have an uncle
in the hotel business!

104
00:13:41,611 --> 00:13:45,012
I admit he's a baron and
the hotel has 500 bedrooms!!!

105
00:13:45,081 --> 00:13:47,174
But you do see the position
it places me in!

106
00:13:47,250 --> 00:13:49,878
[All Laughing]

107
00:13:49,953 --> 00:13:52,387
[Laughing Continues]

108
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,651
[All Chattering, Laughing]

109
00:14:08,371 --> 00:14:11,397
[All Laughing]

110
00:14:11,474 --> 00:14:15,171
¶ There was a town
in Poland ¶

111
00:14:15,245 --> 00:14:19,181
[All] ¶ And there
a girl we found ¶

112
00:14:19,249 --> 00:14:22,514
- ¶ Lovely was she ¶
- Want a cigarette?

113
00:14:22,586 --> 00:14:27,046
- Thank you!
- ¶ She was the haughtiest maid ¶

114
00:14:27,123 --> 00:14:29,717
¶ That ever we beheld ¶

115
00:14:29,793 --> 00:14:32,261
¶ But do not kiss me
please, she said ¶

116
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:34,320
¶ I never kiss ¶

117
00:14:34,397 --> 00:14:36,490
- You've got 18, haven't you?
- ¶¶ [Humming]

118
00:14:36,566 --> 00:14:39,228
Squadron rule number one,
Stachel...

119
00:14:39,302 --> 00:14:41,600
gentlemen never parade
their military achievements!

120
00:14:41,671 --> 00:14:45,232
¶ She was the loveliest maid
that ever we beheld ¶

121
00:14:45,308 --> 00:14:48,436
Any rule against saying
how long it took you?

122
00:14:48,511 --> 00:14:51,708
- ¶¶[Continue Singing]
- I would say that was covered
by the same rule!!!

123
00:14:51,781 --> 00:14:53,772
Wouldn't you?

124
00:14:53,850 --> 00:14:57,308
No, I wouldn't!
How many rules are there?

125
00:14:59,289 --> 00:15:03,123
I don't know!
None of them have been written down!

126
00:15:03,193 --> 00:15:08,790
¶She was the haughtiest maid
that ever we beheld ¶

127
00:15:08,865 --> 00:15:11,484
¶But do not kiss me,
please, she said ¶

128
00:15:11,617 --> 00:15:14,643
¶ I never kiss ¶
[All Laughing]

129
00:15:14,721 --> 00:15:20,216
¶ She was the haughtiest maid
that ever we beheld ¶

130
00:15:20,293 --> 00:15:23,421
- ¶ But do not kiss me, please, she said ¶
- [Horn Honks]

131
00:15:23,496 --> 00:15:25,487
¶ I never kiss ¶¶

132
00:15:25,565 --> 00:15:27,795
¶¶ [Humming]

133
00:15:27,867 --> 00:15:29,858
[Laughing]

134
00:15:32,605 --> 00:15:35,403
- [Laughing]
- Oh!

135
00:15:35,475 --> 00:15:37,466
[Chattering]

136
00:15:37,543 --> 00:15:40,535
[Laughing, Chattering Continue]

137
00:15:49,422 --> 00:15:51,913
Seems you're next to me
in Scholte's old room!

138
00:15:51,991 --> 00:15:56,325
- That's, uh, number 11!
- Scholte?

139
00:15:56,395 --> 00:16:00,456
Oh, your predecessor! He, uh...
He didn't last long, unfortunately!

140
00:16:00,533 --> 00:16:03,969
- Unhappy young man!
- Yes! He forgot to keep
looking over his shoulder!

141
00:16:04,036 --> 00:16:07,164
It's worth remembering!
They come fast, out of the sun!

142
00:16:07,240 --> 00:16:09,902
[Imitating Zooming Noise,
Knife Cutting]

143
00:16:09,976 --> 00:16:11,967
- Thank you!
- [Chuckling]

144
00:16:14,313 --> 00:16:17,146
[Men Chattering, Laughing]

145
00:16:20,153 --> 00:16:23,486
Willi, what do you
think of him?

146
00:16:23,556 --> 00:16:25,547
Hmm?

147
00:16:27,193 --> 00:16:30,026
Gonna have a drink?

148
00:16:30,096 --> 00:16:32,121
- Ah!
- [Chattering]

149
00:17:01,861 --> 00:17:04,295
[Footsteps]

150
00:17:14,407 --> 00:17:18,173
Oh! They haven't removed
poor Scholte's card!

151
00:17:18,244 --> 00:17:20,235
Very tactless of them!

152
00:17:25,351 --> 00:17:29,344
I just thought you should know
we, uh, don't dress for dinner here!

153
00:17:36,929 --> 00:17:39,159
Von Richthofen, I see!

154
00:17:39,232 --> 00:17:41,223
Your hero?

155
00:17:42,635 --> 00:17:45,433
He's done it all!

156
00:17:45,504 --> 00:17:48,735
Two more kills,
and you'll have one of those!

157
00:17:48,808 --> 00:17:52,938
Hmm! A pretty medal,
the Blue Max!

158
00:17:54,513 --> 00:17:57,107
It's the only one worth having!
People respect it!

159
00:17:57,183 --> 00:18:00,084
The medal or the man?

160
00:18:08,961 --> 00:18:12,055
[Door Opens, Closes]

161
00:18:15,902 --> 00:18:18,302
[Birds Chirping]

162
00:18:32,285 --> 00:18:34,981
The usual routine, Fabian!

163
00:18:35,054 --> 00:18:37,045
You know what they are like
the first time in combat!

164
00:18:37,123 --> 00:18:39,455
- Of course!
- Keep your eye on him!

165
00:18:39,525 --> 00:18:43,655
Here! Isn't it nice to hear the birds
again, Herr Hauptmann?

166
00:18:43,729 --> 00:18:46,061
- [Birds Chirping]
- Listen to that!

167
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:49,891
They won't
be here long!

168
00:18:51,971 --> 00:18:55,065
When our offensive starts...
[Spits]

169
00:18:55,141 --> 00:18:57,803
- Good luck, Fabian!
- Herr Hauptmann.

170
00:19:02,248 --> 00:19:04,239
What is it?

171
00:19:05,851 --> 00:19:09,287
Stachel!
Fly on Fabian's left!!!

172
00:19:09,355 --> 00:19:11,448
And a little behind him!

173
00:19:11,524 --> 00:19:14,015
- And watch for his signals!
- Yes, Herr Hauptmann.

174
00:19:14,093 --> 00:19:16,926
And relax! Get the balloon
and come straight back!

175
00:19:16,996 --> 00:19:19,965
- You'll find balloons burn beautifully!
- [Loud Rap]

176
00:19:20,032 --> 00:19:22,660
[Engine Starts In Distance]

177
00:19:24,603 --> 00:19:26,594
Switches on!

178
00:21:25,558 --> 00:21:28,026
[Machine-gun Fire]

179
00:21:30,896 --> 00:21:32,329
[Machine-gun Fire
Continues]

180
00:21:43,209 --> 00:21:45,837
[Artillery Fire]

181
00:22:24,617 --> 00:22:26,608
[Artillery Fire
Continues]

182
00:22:49,808 --> 00:22:51,708
[Machine-gun Fire]

183
00:23:04,223 --> 00:23:06,384
[Machine-gun Fire]

184
00:23:44,096 --> 00:23:46,894
[Machine-gun Fire]

185
00:25:43,716 --> 00:25:47,709
Is that army observation?
Adjutant, Squadron 11 here.

186
00:25:47,786 --> 00:25:51,017
One of our pilots claims
an SE5 shot down in sector five!

187
00:25:51,090 --> 00:25:53,581
- Yes!
- Can you confirm, please?

188
00:25:56,362 --> 00:25:59,160
Yes, about, uh,
0700 hours!

189
00:26:04,203 --> 00:26:08,071
- Perhaps Fabian made a forced landing!
- I don't know!

190
00:26:08,140 --> 00:26:13,442
Yes? Sector five,
on our side of the line!

191
00:26:13,512 --> 00:26:16,447
You did? Fine!

192
00:26:17,449 --> 00:26:19,610
Go on! Uh...

193
00:26:22,087 --> 00:26:24,078
In midair?

194
00:26:25,457 --> 00:26:27,448
- Did yours explode?
- No!

195
00:26:30,429 --> 00:26:33,421
Yes, we do have
a pilot missing!

196
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:37,362
- That will be him, I'm afraid!
- Ask him!

197
00:26:37,436 --> 00:26:40,234
Thanks!
Good-bye!

198
00:26:40,305 --> 00:26:43,604
- But...
- Only Fabian! He never got out!

199
00:26:43,675 --> 00:26:47,839
- No SE5!
- But somebody must have
seen my SE5 go down!

200
00:26:48,881 --> 00:26:51,782
Not necessarily!
[Sighs]

201
00:26:53,385 --> 00:26:55,910
It often happens!

202
00:26:55,988 --> 00:26:58,456
No confirmation, no claim!

203
00:26:58,524 --> 00:27:02,483
- That's a squadron rule!
- But I saw it! It was a kill!

204
00:27:06,498 --> 00:27:10,298
Then you have the deep satisfaction of
knowing you have served the fatherland!

205
00:27:17,075 --> 00:27:19,066
It went down here...
our side of the line!

206
00:27:19,144 --> 00:27:21,135
Why couldn't
the army look for it?

207
00:27:21,213 --> 00:27:23,977
They have other things to do!

208
00:27:24,049 --> 00:27:26,074
Somebody must have seen it!

209
00:27:31,356 --> 00:27:33,347
Fabian might have
seen it!

210
00:27:37,429 --> 00:27:39,420
[Men Chattering]

211
00:27:51,577 --> 00:27:53,568
- Corporal Rupp!
- Herr Leutnant.

212
00:27:53,645 --> 00:27:55,670
We're going to search sector five!
Get your motorcycle!

213
00:27:55,747 --> 00:27:58,375
- But, Herr Leutnant...
- Be at the mess in five minutes!

214
00:27:58,450 --> 00:28:01,442
- Herr Leutnant.
- [Thunder Rumbles]

215
00:28:05,123 --> 00:28:07,819
[Thunder Continues]

216
00:28:10,829 --> 00:28:13,491
[Lowing]

217
00:28:27,946 --> 00:28:30,574
[Starts Engine]

218
00:28:30,649 --> 00:28:32,583
Back to the mess,
Herr Leutnant?

219
00:28:32,651 --> 00:28:35,984
No! I'm going to search
that wood over there!

220
00:28:36,054 --> 00:28:38,545
- You already have, Herr Leutnant.
- What?

221
00:28:38,624 --> 00:28:41,525
You searched that wood
an hour ago!

222
00:28:41,593 --> 00:28:44,756
Well, we're going
to search it again!

223
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:49,358
What's the matter, Rupp?
Too close to the guns for you?

224
00:28:49,434 --> 00:28:51,459
[Engine Revs]

225
00:28:58,410 --> 00:29:01,504
[People Chattering,
Laughing]

226
00:29:18,697 --> 00:29:22,565
- Thank you, Corporal!
- It's been a pleasure, Herr Leutnant.

227
00:29:24,202 --> 00:29:26,193
[Boot Heels Click]

228
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:30,000
[Footsteps]

229
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:35,212
You have finished
your wild goose chase, I hope!

230
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:38,044
- Yes, Herr Hauptmann.
- Found nothing, huh?

231
00:29:39,117 --> 00:29:40,778
No!

232
00:29:43,322 --> 00:29:45,950
If every pilot were to go
careering around France!!!

233
00:29:46,024 --> 00:29:48,151
Looking for
unconfirmed aircraft!!!

234
00:29:48,226 --> 00:29:50,660
There'd be no air force left!

235
00:29:52,364 --> 00:29:54,491
And Corporal Rupp has
more important things to do!

236
00:29:54,566 --> 00:29:57,729
- Do you understand?
- Yes, Herr Hauptmann.

237
00:29:57,803 --> 00:30:02,831
Unconfirmed by army
means unconfirmed, and that's final!

238
00:30:02,908 --> 00:30:05,399
Good night, Stachel!

239
00:30:12,084 --> 00:30:15,076
- ¶¶[Piano]
- [Chattering, Laughing]

240
00:30:17,255 --> 00:30:20,099
Stachel!

241
00:30:20,232 --> 00:30:22,132
Come and join us!

242
00:30:26,272 --> 00:30:28,900
- Ah!
- [Laughing]

243
00:30:28,974 --> 00:30:30,965
I'll get the next one, Willi!

244
00:30:35,381 --> 00:30:38,077
- Brandy, please!
- Champagne, Herr Leutnant.

245
00:30:38,150 --> 00:30:40,141
Willi got his 20th kill today!

246
00:30:40,219 --> 00:30:43,211
- He's being awarded the Blue Max!
- Uh-huh!

247
00:30:45,825 --> 00:30:47,986
I see you've had
a hard day!

248
00:30:49,662 --> 00:30:52,859
No one's ever done that before
about an unconfirmed kill!

249
00:30:52,932 --> 00:30:56,231
Quite novel!
You must be in a hurry!

250
00:30:59,538 --> 00:31:01,529
To your Blue Max!

251
00:31:01,607 --> 00:31:04,337
- Blue Max!
- Willi!

252
00:31:04,410 --> 00:31:07,504
- [Men Chattering]
- [Billiard Balls Clacking]

253
00:31:07,580 --> 00:31:10,071
I don't suppose you've ever had
an unconfirmed kill!

254
00:31:10,149 --> 00:31:13,448
Oh, but I have!
I've had, uh, three!

255
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,711
Then you've shot down 23!

256
00:31:16,789 --> 00:31:19,519
No!

257
00:31:19,592 --> 00:31:21,583
- Twenty!
- [Laughing]

258
00:31:25,498 --> 00:31:27,489
By the way, Stachel!!!

259
00:31:27,566 --> 00:31:30,194
There's an impression
around that!!!

260
00:31:30,269 --> 00:31:33,966
You care more about
your unconfirmed kill!!!

261
00:31:34,039 --> 00:31:36,599
Than you do
about Fabian's death!

262
00:31:36,675 --> 00:31:39,007
[All Quiet]

263
00:31:47,420 --> 00:31:49,445
Perhaps it's force of habit!

264
00:31:51,157 --> 00:31:54,149
In the trenches,
we couldn't even bury the dead!

265
00:31:55,361 --> 00:31:57,352
There were too many of them!

266
00:31:58,898 --> 00:32:01,196
I've never had the time!!!

267
00:32:01,267 --> 00:32:03,827
To discuss them over
a glass of champagne!

268
00:32:03,903 --> 00:32:07,862
[Chuckling]
Well, never mind, Stachel!

269
00:32:07,940 --> 00:32:10,636
To your unconfirmed victory!

270
00:32:10,709 --> 00:32:13,439
Next time,
you must have witnesses!

271
00:32:13,512 --> 00:32:15,844
- Witnesses!
- Witnesses!

272
00:32:15,915 --> 00:32:18,247
- Good evening, gentlemen!
- [Man] Good evening.

273
00:32:18,317 --> 00:32:20,308
Pairings for next week's sorties!

274
00:32:21,587 --> 00:32:23,578
- Let's have them, please!
- I'll fly with Becker!

275
00:32:23,656 --> 00:32:25,647
- [Man] Heller and Braun!
- [Second Man] I'll fly with Lindorf!

276
00:32:25,724 --> 00:32:27,954
[Third Man] Von Klinger and I
will do the ground strafe!

277
00:32:30,429 --> 00:32:33,762
Good!
Who'll fly with Stachel?

278
00:33:04,230 --> 00:33:06,289
I'll fly with Stachel!

279
00:34:03,956 --> 00:34:06,789
[Machine-gun Fire]

280
00:37:01,033 --> 00:37:04,469
He's...
He's bringing her in!

281
00:37:47,613 --> 00:37:49,911
[Crash]

282
00:37:51,383 --> 00:37:54,045
[Klaxon Blaring]

283
00:37:56,588 --> 00:37:59,250
[Men Shouting, Indistinct]

284
00:38:00,325 --> 00:38:02,816
This one is dead,
Herr Leutnant.

285
00:38:06,765 --> 00:38:10,929
- Easy, easy!
- [Man] Bring a stretcher!
Quick! Quick!

286
00:38:11,003 --> 00:38:13,801
- Get over there!
- Quickly!

287
00:38:41,633 --> 00:38:43,965
What happened, Stachel?

288
00:38:47,105 --> 00:38:50,097
The observer, he was
going to open fire!

289
00:38:54,379 --> 00:38:58,042
Then we are to assume
he was either very brave!!!

290
00:38:58,116 --> 00:39:00,710
Or very foolish!

291
00:39:48,267 --> 00:39:50,428
Confirmed!

292
00:39:52,471 --> 00:39:56,464
It's a cruel world, Herr Hauptmann.
You said so yourself!

293
00:40:14,259 --> 00:40:16,887
[Man Shouting, Indistinct]

294
00:40:28,707 --> 00:40:30,675
Willi!

295
00:40:42,254 --> 00:40:45,781
I've read your report, Willi!
What really happened?

296
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:51,327
As I said, Otto, the observer
made a move for his gun!!!

297
00:40:51,396 --> 00:40:53,387
So Stachel
shot him down!

298
00:40:53,465 --> 00:40:56,059
You wish to stand by
a comrade!

299
00:40:56,134 --> 00:41:00,230
- I appreciate that!
- What I reported is what I saw!

300
00:41:00,305 --> 00:41:03,297
We are German officers!
We'll fight this war with chivalry!

301
00:41:03,375 --> 00:41:06,367
- You know that as well as I do!
- Of course!

302
00:41:10,115 --> 00:41:14,279
The observer was blinded!
Did you know that?

303
00:41:16,021 --> 00:41:19,855
No! It could have happened
when Stachel opened fire over the airfield!

304
00:41:19,925 --> 00:41:21,916
- But did it?
- I don't know!

305
00:41:21,994 --> 00:41:25,293
You know how Stachel behaved
when his first claim was disallowed!

306
00:41:28,700 --> 00:41:32,431
If he shot down
a helpless enemy in cold blood!!!

307
00:41:32,504 --> 00:41:35,302
It's something I won't tolerate
in my squadron!

308
00:41:37,242 --> 00:41:42,111
All right, I agree!
There is some measure of doubt!

309
00:41:42,180 --> 00:41:44,842
But I have no reason
to change my report!

310
00:41:55,861 --> 00:41:57,920
All right, Willi!

311
00:41:57,996 --> 00:42:01,124
The incident is closed,
officially anyway!

312
00:42:06,872 --> 00:42:08,863
Is everyone here?

313
00:42:11,209 --> 00:42:14,201
All except Leutnant Stachel,
Herr Hauptmann.

314
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:18,611
Someone inform him
this is a parade!

315
00:42:18,683 --> 00:42:21,151
He is ordered
to attend!

316
00:42:27,225 --> 00:42:29,216
[Knocking]

317
00:42:32,431 --> 00:42:34,422
We're about
to honor your dead!

318
00:42:35,801 --> 00:42:37,792
So I see!

319
00:42:42,941 --> 00:42:45,739
Well, aren't
you coming?

320
00:42:47,145 --> 00:42:49,136
It's an order!

321
00:42:50,282 --> 00:42:52,273
Why?

322
00:42:52,350 --> 00:42:55,080
Because our commanding officer
has made it one!

323
00:42:55,153 --> 00:42:58,680
He believes in chivalry, Stachel.

324
00:42:58,757 --> 00:43:00,748
Chivalry?

325
00:43:02,594 --> 00:43:04,585
To kill a man!!!

326
00:43:04,663 --> 00:43:07,723
Then make a ritual
out of saluting him?

327
00:43:07,799 --> 00:43:10,893
That's hypocrisy!

328
00:43:10,969 --> 00:43:13,199
- They kill me!!!
- [Glass Clinks, Drink Pours]

329
00:43:13,271 --> 00:43:15,637
I don't want
anyone to salute!

330
00:43:15,707 --> 00:43:19,143
- [Glass Slams]
- They probably won't!

331
00:43:28,086 --> 00:43:30,077
All right!

332
00:43:34,392 --> 00:43:36,883
Let's get it over with,
shall we?

333
00:43:37,429 --> 00:43:39,420
Stachel!

334
00:43:42,868 --> 00:43:45,234
Thank you!

335
00:43:45,303 --> 00:43:48,500
You know, there's something
of the cobra in you!

336
00:43:52,377 --> 00:43:54,368
I'll have to watch you!

337
00:43:56,281 --> 00:43:58,613
Mm-hmm!

338
00:43:58,683 --> 00:44:00,981
[Chuckling]

339
00:44:02,754 --> 00:44:05,723
¶¶[Martial]

340
00:44:09,027 --> 00:44:11,018
Leutnant von Klugermann!

341
00:44:15,867 --> 00:44:18,301
Parade, stand at!!! Ease!

342
00:44:22,641 --> 00:44:26,543
I assume you've talked
to the other pilots about this, Holbach!

343
00:44:26,611 --> 00:44:29,944
Yes, Herr General. I'm making a thorough
inquiry into the whole incident!

344
00:44:30,015 --> 00:44:32,176
Good!

345
00:44:32,250 --> 00:44:34,616
When the opportunity arises,
point the man out to me!

346
00:44:34,686 --> 00:44:36,677
Yes, Herr General.

347
00:44:38,256 --> 00:44:40,247
- Ah, Otto!
- [Boot Heels Click]

348
00:44:40,325 --> 00:44:42,316
The squadron's drawn up,
Herr General.

349
00:44:42,394 --> 00:44:44,885
We were discussing the pilot
who brought this in!

350
00:44:44,963 --> 00:44:47,693
Air headquarters
is quite excited about it!

351
00:44:47,766 --> 00:44:50,326
What's the man's name again?

352
00:44:50,402 --> 00:44:52,893
- Leutnant Stachel, Herr General.
- Mm-hmm!

353
00:44:55,106 --> 00:44:57,097
Is he a good flyer?

354
00:44:58,176 --> 00:45:00,838
Yes! Yes, he is!

355
00:45:02,814 --> 00:45:06,944
Glad to hear it! We mustn't
keep my nephew waiting any longer!

356
00:45:07,018 --> 00:45:09,189
Not to mention my wife!

357
00:45:09,322 --> 00:45:11,756
¶¶ [Continues]

358
00:45:22,536 --> 00:45:25,300
[Man]
Parade, front!

359
00:45:25,372 --> 00:45:27,863
Left... turn!

360
00:45:34,114 --> 00:45:37,641
Sorry to have been so long!
Were you bored?

361
00:45:37,717 --> 00:45:39,708
With all these men around?

362
00:45:40,954 --> 00:45:43,184
Look beautiful for them, Kaeti!

363
00:45:44,925 --> 00:45:46,984
Look at Willi!

364
00:45:47,060 --> 00:45:49,722
Doesn't he look splendid?

365
00:45:49,796 --> 00:45:52,424
The Blue Max
will go so well with his eyes!

366
00:45:52,499 --> 00:45:54,490
He is rather vain!

367
00:45:54,568 --> 00:45:57,093
He'll probably wear it in bed
the first few days!

368
00:45:57,170 --> 00:45:59,400
Oh, how uncomfortable
for the girl!

369
00:45:59,473 --> 00:46:02,499
- [Man] Parade... attention!
- Excuse me, Herr General.

370
00:46:02,576 --> 00:46:04,703
- Yes?
- The second one on the left!!!

371
00:46:04,778 --> 00:46:07,246
Front row... that's Stachel!

372
00:46:13,620 --> 00:46:15,645
- Ah!
- ¶¶[Concludes]

373
00:46:17,791 --> 00:46:20,453
"To Leutnant Wilhem von Klugermann!!!

374
00:46:20,527 --> 00:46:23,189
"For bravery
of the highest order!!!

375
00:46:23,263 --> 00:46:26,960
"In action against the enemies
of the German Empire...

376
00:46:27,033 --> 00:46:30,662
"and for exceptional services
to the fatherland...

377
00:46:30,737 --> 00:46:35,800
"in that he has destroyed
single-handed 20 enemy aircraft...

378
00:46:35,876 --> 00:46:39,175
"the order Pour Le Mérite!

379
00:46:39,246 --> 00:46:41,237
"By imperial decree...

380
00:46:41,314 --> 00:46:44,147
Wilhem, Emperor!"

381
00:46:53,460 --> 00:46:56,759
I'm afraid it's rather
a small medal, Willi!!!

382
00:46:58,632 --> 00:47:00,930
But it's the highest
Germany can give!

383
00:47:02,102 --> 00:47:04,195
Thank you!!! Uncle!

384
00:47:04,938 --> 00:47:06,929
[Boot Heels Click]

385
00:47:12,279 --> 00:47:13,513
- ¶¶[Orchestra]
- [Laughing]

386
00:47:13,513 --> 00:47:15,413
- ¶¶[Orchestra]
- [Laughing]

387
00:47:17,651 --> 00:47:21,109
[Loud Chatter]

388
00:47:21,187 --> 00:47:23,781
- ¶¶[Men Singing]
- [Cork Pops]

389
00:47:28,828 --> 00:47:30,819
Otto!

390
00:47:30,897 --> 00:47:33,525
This pilot of yours...
Stachel!

391
00:47:33,600 --> 00:47:37,263
Humble origin, risen from the ranks,
et cetera, et cetera!

392
00:47:37,337 --> 00:47:40,363
Two years'
front-line service, hmm?

393
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:42,408
Yes, that's right!

394
00:47:42,475 --> 00:47:46,935
To deliver the final blow over your own
airfield... on the doorstep, so to speak!

395
00:47:47,013 --> 00:47:50,073
- It was splendid, wasn't it?
- "Splendid"?

396
00:47:50,150 --> 00:47:53,551
Otto, if this young man
lives long enough!!!

397
00:47:53,620 --> 00:47:56,680
He could be very useful
to our propaganda department!

398
00:47:56,756 --> 00:48:00,817
The common people of our country
are war-weary, restive!

399
00:48:00,894 --> 00:48:03,385
They need to be provided
with a hero of their own!

400
00:48:03,463 --> 00:48:07,092
Von Richthofen, Willi,
are of our class!

401
00:48:07,167 --> 00:48:10,728
That fellow Stachel is common as dirt!
He's one of them!

402
00:48:10,804 --> 00:48:13,671
- You understand?
- Yes, I understand!

403
00:48:15,175 --> 00:48:17,666
But I don't agree with
killing helpless men!

404
00:48:17,744 --> 00:48:21,612
Otto, this is 1918!
Things have changed!

405
00:48:21,681 --> 00:48:24,343
Unrestricted submarine warfare!
Bombing of civilians!

406
00:48:24,417 --> 00:48:26,977
Poison gas!
Ask your wife... she's a nurse!

407
00:48:27,053 --> 00:48:30,045
Ask Elfi about
the mustard gas casualties!

408
00:48:35,562 --> 00:48:38,360
So you approve
of this kind of ruthlessness!

409
00:48:40,333 --> 00:48:44,702
- We fight to win, Otto!
- Yes, of course!

410
00:48:46,306 --> 00:48:48,866
Excuse me, Herr General.

411
00:48:48,942 --> 00:48:51,775
[Holbach]
Herr General!

412
00:48:51,845 --> 00:48:54,541
May I present
Leutnant Stachel!

413
00:48:54,614 --> 00:48:56,605
[Boot Heels Click]

414
00:48:58,618 --> 00:49:00,984
I saw the plane
which you brought in!

415
00:49:02,455 --> 00:49:06,516
Very!!!
Interesting exploit!

416
00:49:06,593 --> 00:49:09,528
It proves that our young men
still have vitality!!!

417
00:49:09,596 --> 00:49:13,225
Courage and the will to win
at all costs!

418
00:49:15,335 --> 00:49:18,361
Yes, Herr General.
Thank you!

419
00:49:20,073 --> 00:49:22,234
I'm sure we'll hear
a lot more of you!

420
00:49:22,308 --> 00:49:24,299
[Boot Heels Click]

421
00:49:25,745 --> 00:49:28,908
[Loud Chatter, Laughing]

422
00:49:33,086 --> 00:49:36,487
Kaeti, you haven't met
our Leutnant Stachel!

423
00:49:36,556 --> 00:49:38,581
Stachel.

424
00:49:38,658 --> 00:49:41,149
May I introduce
the Countess von Klugermann!

425
00:49:41,227 --> 00:49:43,354
[Boot Heels Click]

426
00:49:43,430 --> 00:49:46,399
My aunt!!!
By marriage!

427
00:49:47,600 --> 00:49:50,797
You appear to have caught
my uncle's interest!

428
00:49:50,870 --> 00:49:53,839
Interest from high places
is always welcome!

429
00:49:54,841 --> 00:49:56,832
May I get you a drink,
Countess?

430
00:49:58,545 --> 00:50:01,776
All right!
Champagne!

431
00:50:01,848 --> 00:50:04,578
Champagne!

432
00:50:04,651 --> 00:50:07,745
Pink champagne!
[Laughing]

433
00:50:07,821 --> 00:50:10,187
- Pink champagne?
- Yes!

434
00:50:12,292 --> 00:50:14,760
Yes, Countess!

435
00:50:14,828 --> 00:50:17,023
[No Audible Dialogue]

436
00:50:17,097 --> 00:50:20,794
- May I have two glasses
of pink champagne, please?
- [Loud Chattering]

437
00:50:20,867 --> 00:50:23,768
[Louder] May I have two glasses
of pink champagne, please?

438
00:50:23,837 --> 00:50:26,305
- ¶¶[Waltz]
- Well, I say...

439
00:50:26,372 --> 00:50:29,205
My glass, hmm?

440
00:50:29,275 --> 00:50:31,869
- ¶¶[Men Vocalizing To Music]
- [Laughing]

441
00:50:31,945 --> 00:50:34,971
¶La-la-la la-la-la ¶

442
00:50:35,048 --> 00:50:38,347
¶La-la-la la-la ¶

443
00:50:38,418 --> 00:50:41,615
¶ La-la-la la-la-la ¶

444
00:50:41,688 --> 00:50:44,782
- ¶La-la-la la-la-la ¶
- [Laughing]

445
00:50:44,858 --> 00:50:47,554
¶ Yam-pah-pah
yam-pah-pah ¶

446
00:50:47,627 --> 00:50:50,858
That champagne
is getting warm, Stachel!

447
00:50:50,930 --> 00:50:53,262
¶¶[Vocalizing Continues]

448
00:50:53,333 --> 00:50:55,324
Not yet!

449
00:50:55,401 --> 00:50:57,460
[Laughing]

450
00:50:57,537 --> 00:51:01,997
¶La-la-la-la
la-la-la la-la-la-la ¶¶

451
00:51:02,075 --> 00:51:04,407
Silence, please!
Silence!

452
00:51:04,477 --> 00:51:06,945
- Please, silence!
- ¶¶[Stops]

453
00:51:13,853 --> 00:51:15,844
Gentlemen!!!

454
00:51:15,922 --> 00:51:18,220
In a few hours!!!

455
00:51:19,659 --> 00:51:24,187
The horizon will be lit up
by the flashes of 7,000 guns!

456
00:51:24,264 --> 00:51:26,255
Our guns!

457
00:51:26,332 --> 00:51:28,459
[All Cheering]

458
00:51:28,535 --> 00:51:31,231
[Cheering Subsides]

459
00:51:31,304 --> 00:51:35,866
They will herald
the greatest offensive in history!

460
00:51:37,977 --> 00:51:40,605
Our defeat of Russia
has released a million men...

461
00:51:40,680 --> 00:51:42,671
for the Western Front!

462
00:51:42,749 --> 00:51:44,774
I need hardly tell you!!!

463
00:51:44,851 --> 00:51:49,220
That if we destroy the British
and French armies...

464
00:51:49,289 --> 00:51:53,726
before the Americans
can intervene effectively!!!

465
00:51:53,793 --> 00:51:55,886
We shall have
won the war!

466
00:51:55,962 --> 00:51:59,227
- [All Cheering]
- God be with us! God be with us!

467
00:51:59,299 --> 00:52:03,030
¶¶[Martial]

468
00:52:03,102 --> 00:52:05,627
[No Audible Dialogue]

469
00:52:28,428 --> 00:52:30,589
[Light Footsteps]

470
00:52:30,663 --> 00:52:32,654
[Door Opens]

471
00:52:34,100 --> 00:52:37,035
[Hushed]
Oh! Willi, darling!

472
00:52:37,103 --> 00:52:39,401
- [Door Closes]
- Mm-hmm!

473
00:52:39,472 --> 00:52:41,770
I'm sorry I'm late!

474
00:52:43,209 --> 00:52:45,643
[Yelps]

475
00:52:45,712 --> 00:52:47,942
[Chuckling]
I'm sorry!

476
00:52:49,182 --> 00:52:51,173
Well, I'm not!

477
00:52:51,251 --> 00:52:55,119
If you're looking for your nephew,
he's next door!

478
00:52:55,188 --> 00:52:58,555
Yes!
I realize that now!

479
00:53:05,198 --> 00:53:08,099
[Clears Throat]
As long as you're here!!!

480
00:53:08,167 --> 00:53:10,192
Perhaps I can
get you that drink!

481
00:53:10,270 --> 00:53:12,261
Yes, do!

482
00:53:12,338 --> 00:53:14,772
I'm afraid
I'm out of champagne!

483
00:53:14,841 --> 00:53:17,571
- Then whatever you have!
- Schnapps!

484
00:53:27,887 --> 00:53:30,788
Mmm! Horrible!!!

485
00:53:30,857 --> 00:53:33,155
But quite stimulating!

486
00:53:44,637 --> 00:53:46,969
So that's you... Cobra!

487
00:53:47,040 --> 00:53:51,306
- "Cobra"?
- Yes! That's what Willi calls you!

488
00:53:54,247 --> 00:53:56,909
Has he been talking
about me to you?

489
00:53:58,284 --> 00:54:00,718
I asked!

490
00:54:00,787 --> 00:54:03,915
He says you're quite,
uh, deadly!!!

491
00:54:03,990 --> 00:54:06,754
In sort of a quiet way!

492
00:54:06,826 --> 00:54:10,922
[Chuckles]
He's a romantic!

493
00:54:10,997 --> 00:54:13,932
- And you're not!
- No!

494
00:54:15,101 --> 00:54:17,092
No!

495
00:54:17,170 --> 00:54:20,606
Tonight is a!!!
Family affair!

496
00:54:21,975 --> 00:54:24,068
[Laughing]

497
00:54:28,748 --> 00:54:32,514
- Are you shocked?
- No!

498
00:54:32,585 --> 00:54:37,716
- You see, my husband is a very civilized man!!!
- Mmm!

499
00:54:37,790 --> 00:54:40,156
And we are great friends!

500
00:54:40,226 --> 00:54:42,888
It must be nice to have
an understanding friend!

501
00:54:42,962 --> 00:54:45,362
Oh, yes, it is!

502
00:54:48,534 --> 00:54:51,526
Willi must be
getting impatient!

503
00:54:51,604 --> 00:54:53,663
Shall I announce you?

504
00:54:54,674 --> 00:54:56,642
Please do!

505
00:54:57,944 --> 00:54:59,969
[Pounding]

506
00:55:01,447 --> 00:55:03,574
[Pounding]

507
00:55:04,384 --> 00:55:06,375
Thank you!

508
00:55:14,360 --> 00:55:16,954
[Laughing]

509
00:55:24,003 --> 00:55:27,564
- [Faint Knocking]
- [Door Opens, Closes]

510
00:55:28,574 --> 00:55:30,565
[Countess Laughing]

511
00:55:37,817 --> 00:55:41,753
[Artillery Fire In Distance]

512
00:56:44,390 --> 00:56:46,654
[Artillery Fire In Distance]

513
00:57:04,543 --> 00:57:07,569
[Artillery Fire Continues]

514
00:57:17,089 --> 00:57:21,025
[Machine-gun Fire]

515
00:57:21,093 --> 00:57:25,587
- [Gunfire, Explosions]
- [Shouting, Indistinct]

516
00:57:30,402 --> 00:57:32,393
[Man] Fire!

517
00:57:52,591 --> 00:57:54,616
[All Shouting, Indistinct]

518
00:58:02,868 --> 00:58:05,302
[Man] Fire!

519
00:58:17,249 --> 00:58:20,241
- [Machine-gun Fire]
- Come on, lads! This is it!

520
00:58:38,237 --> 00:58:40,933
[Man]
Follow me!

521
00:58:49,448 --> 00:58:51,678
[Machine-gun Fire]

522
00:58:53,285 --> 00:58:55,753
[Incoming Shells Whistling]

523
00:59:04,029 --> 00:59:05,519
[Man]
Here they come again!

524
00:59:12,104 --> 00:59:14,368
[All Shouting, Indistinct]

525
00:59:19,445 --> 00:59:21,640
[Screams]

526
00:59:27,553 --> 00:59:29,145
[Groans]

527
00:59:35,394 --> 00:59:37,760
[Man] Come on, boys!
Come on now!

528
00:59:49,909 --> 00:59:52,002
[Whistle Blows]

529
00:59:52,077 --> 00:59:55,410
[Airplanes Droning]

530
01:00:35,821 --> 01:00:39,018
[Machine-gun Fire]

531
01:00:54,306 --> 01:00:56,866
[Machine-gun Fire
Continues]

532
01:01:19,331 --> 01:01:21,231
[Machine-gun Fire]

533
01:01:35,714 --> 01:01:38,114
[Explosion]

534
01:01:49,828 --> 01:01:52,228
The oil pressure's
still too low!

535
01:01:52,297 --> 01:01:54,731
That's all you'll
get out of her!

536
01:01:54,800 --> 01:01:56,791
She wasn't made yesterday!

537
01:01:57,970 --> 01:02:00,461
Oh, is that what it is?

538
01:03:02,568 --> 01:03:05,093
[Machine-gun Fire]

539
01:03:17,516 --> 01:03:20,212
[Machine-gun Fire]

540
01:03:42,107 --> 01:03:45,565
[Machine-gun Fire]

541
01:03:48,580 --> 01:03:50,241
[Machine-gun Fire]

542
01:04:21,146 --> 01:04:23,239
[Neighing]

543
01:04:36,461 --> 01:04:38,395
[Engine Stalling]

544
01:05:33,719 --> 01:05:36,415
[Airplane Droning]

545
01:05:45,097 --> 01:05:47,588
[No Audible Dialogue]

546
01:06:06,885 --> 01:06:10,582
[Explosions In Distance]

547
01:06:20,565 --> 01:06:23,728
- [Groans]
- You'll feel better in
a few days, Herr Leutnant.

548
01:06:25,003 --> 01:06:27,437
- We've taken Bapaume!
- Bapaume!

549
01:06:27,506 --> 01:06:29,497
Bapaume!

550
01:06:30,709 --> 01:06:33,303
[Groans] It means
we're closer to Paris!

551
01:06:37,049 --> 01:06:39,040
Thank you!

552
01:06:39,117 --> 01:06:41,108
Herr Leutnant, I'm here
to take you back to the squadron!

553
01:06:41,186 --> 01:06:43,177
In there, Herr Leutnant.

554
01:06:53,332 --> 01:06:55,994
What are we celebrating?

555
01:06:56,068 --> 01:06:59,970
Your survival, of course,
and your tenth victory!

556
01:07:00,038 --> 01:07:02,029
You're moving up fast,
Stachel!

557
01:07:02,107 --> 01:07:04,302
Too fast?

558
01:07:06,244 --> 01:07:08,371
[Artillery Fire Continues]

559
01:07:11,083 --> 01:07:13,244
Does it hurt?

560
01:07:13,318 --> 01:07:15,309
Yes!

561
01:07:17,222 --> 01:07:19,713
Then I'd better
open the bottle!

562
01:07:31,169 --> 01:07:33,194
Tell me, uh...

563
01:07:33,271 --> 01:07:36,399
never having
suffered it personally...

564
01:07:36,475 --> 01:07:39,638
what does it feel like
to be!!! Shot down?

565
01:07:39,711 --> 01:07:44,045
- I'd rather you found that out for yourself!
- [Chuckles]

566
01:07:44,116 --> 01:07:46,983
¶¶ [Humming]

567
01:07:51,623 --> 01:07:53,614
Prosit.

568
01:07:57,062 --> 01:07:59,553
You know, l... I was
quite pleased at first...

569
01:07:59,631 --> 01:08:01,622
when you were posted
missing, I mean!

570
01:08:01,700 --> 01:08:03,998
Thank you!

571
01:08:04,069 --> 01:08:06,469
Oh, it was just that, uh,
all of a sudden!!!

572
01:08:06,538 --> 01:08:09,564
The war seemed
a bit more!!! Peaceful!

573
01:08:09,641 --> 01:08:13,441
And then... this is the odd thing...
I had a sense of loss!

574
01:08:13,512 --> 01:08:16,572
- I'm touched!
- No, no! Uh, seriously!

575
01:08:16,648 --> 01:08:20,084
I suppose I've had everything
in my life too easy!

576
01:08:20,152 --> 01:08:22,143
I'm inclined to be lazy!

577
01:08:22,220 --> 01:08:26,213
I have to have a challenge!
I need someone around me who is, uh!!!

578
01:08:26,291 --> 01:08:28,691
Hard to beat!!!

579
01:08:28,760 --> 01:08:31,354
And you fulfill that role!

580
01:08:32,864 --> 01:08:35,059
- How's the countess?
- The countess?

581
01:08:35,133 --> 01:08:37,124
- Mmm!
- Oh!

582
01:08:39,237 --> 01:08:41,296
Your aunt by marriage!

583
01:08:41,373 --> 01:08:43,364
- Is she well?
- I think so!

584
01:08:43,442 --> 01:08:46,138
I should have thought
you'd have known!

585
01:08:46,211 --> 01:08:50,875
Oh, yes! She told me about
coming into your room that night!

586
01:08:50,949 --> 01:08:53,713
I knew you'd have
to bring it up sooner or later!

587
01:08:53,785 --> 01:08:56,720
The countess!

588
01:08:56,788 --> 01:09:00,554
- [Smacks Lips]
- There's a fascinating subject!

589
01:09:03,195 --> 01:09:06,892
I believe you have aspirations
in that direction, Stachel!

590
01:09:06,965 --> 01:09:09,490
You should forget them!

591
01:09:09,568 --> 01:09:11,559
I'll try!

592
01:09:12,804 --> 01:09:16,035
But if the impossible happens!!!

593
01:09:16,107 --> 01:09:19,099
I'll buy you
a bottle of champagne!

594
01:09:19,177 --> 01:09:21,168
Will you?

595
01:09:22,180 --> 01:09:24,375
It's vintage 1903!

596
01:09:25,851 --> 01:09:28,820
You'll find it!!!
Hard to get!

597
01:09:28,887 --> 01:09:30,878
[Chuckles]

598
01:09:32,424 --> 01:09:36,417
1903? I'll remember that!

599
01:09:36,495 --> 01:09:38,656
[Gears Shifting]

600
01:09:42,567 --> 01:09:44,558
[Brakes Squeal]

601
01:09:47,606 --> 01:09:49,597
Thanks for the champagne!

602
01:09:49,674 --> 01:09:51,904
[Groans]

603
01:09:54,045 --> 01:09:56,386
That's the damn fool
that almost got me killed today!

604
01:09:56,519 --> 01:09:58,384
I believe he's a friend of mine!

605
01:09:58,455 --> 01:10:00,787
Why don't you
take it up with him?

606
01:10:00,857 --> 01:10:02,848
I hope it'll be
a longer visit next time!

607
01:10:02,926 --> 01:10:04,917
Yes, of course! Stachel!

608
01:10:04,995 --> 01:10:07,395
May I introduce!!!

609
01:10:07,464 --> 01:10:10,228
The Baron von Richthofen!

610
01:10:13,169 --> 01:10:15,160
It is an honor,
Herr Rittmeister.

611
01:10:15,238 --> 01:10:18,674
And I'm very grateful!
Hmm!

612
01:10:18,742 --> 01:10:21,973
1903 again!

613
01:10:22,045 --> 01:10:25,242
- [All Chuckling]
- You'll never change, Willi!

614
01:10:25,315 --> 01:10:27,783
I'd like to have some
of Willi's champagne with you!!!

615
01:10:27,851 --> 01:10:30,342
But I must get back
to my squadron!

616
01:10:31,554 --> 01:10:33,749
I'm glad to see
you haven't had to pay!!!

617
01:10:33,823 --> 01:10:36,553
Too high a price
for my life!

618
01:10:36,626 --> 01:10:39,993
I only lost an old Pfalz,
Herr Rittmeister.

619
01:10:40,063 --> 01:10:42,827
Perhaps now I'll get
a better plane!

620
01:10:42,899 --> 01:10:45,891
Oh, yes, you will!

621
01:10:45,969 --> 01:10:49,700
My squadron is going to be equipped
with the new monoplane!!!

622
01:10:49,773 --> 01:10:52,298
Berlin's been
promising so long!

623
01:10:52,375 --> 01:10:54,434
I don't understand,
Herr Rittmeister.

624
01:10:57,280 --> 01:11:00,579
The baron wants you
to join his squadron, Stachel!

625
01:11:00,650 --> 01:11:02,641
I have no objection!

626
01:11:02,719 --> 01:11:05,210
Well, what do you think?

627
01:11:07,590 --> 01:11:11,526
I am!!! Very flattered by your offer,
Herr Rittmeister.

628
01:11:11,594 --> 01:11:13,585
Thank you!

629
01:11:13,663 --> 01:11:17,155
But I'd prefer
to prove myself here!

630
01:11:17,233 --> 01:11:19,463
Oh, I see!

631
01:11:19,536 --> 01:11:22,471
Well, I admire loyalty!

632
01:11:30,780 --> 01:11:32,907
You're lucky to have
this fellow, Otto!

633
01:11:32,982 --> 01:11:34,973
[Man]
Switches on!

634
01:11:35,051 --> 01:11:37,042
[Engine Starts]

635
01:11:37,987 --> 01:11:39,978
[No Audible Dialogue]

636
01:11:40,056 --> 01:11:42,183
Thank you!

637
01:11:59,075 --> 01:12:01,566
[Chattering]

638
01:12:19,896 --> 01:12:21,887
Holbach!!!

639
01:12:21,965 --> 01:12:24,627
Bring me that report
from Von Richthofen again!

640
01:12:24,701 --> 01:12:26,692
Yes, Herr General.

641
01:12:26,770 --> 01:12:29,204
You're not
shoeing a horse!

642
01:12:29,272 --> 01:12:31,263
Get out!

643
01:12:31,341 --> 01:12:33,332
Herr General.

644
01:12:47,824 --> 01:12:50,224
Stachel!

645
01:12:50,293 --> 01:12:53,626
I want him brought to Berlin
immediately!

646
01:12:53,696 --> 01:12:55,789
- Yes, Herr General.
- There is some difficulty?

647
01:12:57,133 --> 01:13:00,068
[Chuckling] I don't know
what you have in mind!!!

648
01:13:00,136 --> 01:13:02,730
But with the offensive
at its height!!!

649
01:13:02,806 --> 01:13:04,797
There'd have to be
some legitimate excuse!!!

650
01:13:04,874 --> 01:13:06,865
To order him
from the front.

651
01:13:06,943 --> 01:13:10,106
- He's wounded, isn't he?
- Yes, Herr General.

652
01:13:10,180 --> 01:13:13,343
Hmm!
A mentionable wound?

653
01:13:13,416 --> 01:13:15,680
In the arm!

654
01:13:15,752 --> 01:13:19,483
Good! The people like soldiers
to be shot in the right places!

655
01:13:19,556 --> 01:13:22,582
Order Stachel to Berlin
for special hospital treatment!

656
01:13:22,659 --> 01:13:25,457
I want you to ensure that all
our newspapers give full prominence!!!

657
01:13:25,528 --> 01:13:28,793
To this!!!
Gallant episode!

658
01:13:28,865 --> 01:13:32,028
Photographs!
Everything!

659
01:13:32,101 --> 01:13:34,092
Yes, Herr General.

660
01:13:34,170 --> 01:13:36,161
Yes!

661
01:13:36,239 --> 01:13:40,869
I think I can get the field marshal
to see things my way!!!

662
01:13:40,944 --> 01:13:43,139
With luck!

663
01:13:43,213 --> 01:13:46,808
[Wind Rushing]

664
01:13:46,883 --> 01:13:49,943
- [Man] Stop!
- [Wind Machine Shuts Down]

665
01:13:57,393 --> 01:13:59,452
So what you're telling me
behind your jargon!!!

666
01:13:59,529 --> 01:14:01,554
Is that this machine
is unstable!

667
01:14:01,631 --> 01:14:03,690
Exactly!
Herr Field Marshal!!!

668
01:14:03,766 --> 01:14:07,668
We require at least three more months
to perfect the design!

669
01:14:07,737 --> 01:14:10,228
By then, the war
may well be lost!

670
01:14:16,946 --> 01:14:21,383
Well, Franz, what more have you
to say to the experts?

671
01:14:21,451 --> 01:14:23,442
With your permission,
Herr Field Marshal!!!

672
01:14:23,519 --> 01:14:26,044
I would like to produce
an expert of my own!

673
01:14:27,390 --> 01:14:29,017
[Man] Stachel!

674
01:14:33,730 --> 01:14:37,598
We would like the benefit
of your experience, Stachel.

675
01:14:37,667 --> 01:14:41,569
You'll have read in this morning's papers
about Von Richthofen!

676
01:14:41,638 --> 01:14:45,904
- This is the pilot concerned...
Leutnant Bruno Stachel!
- [Boot Heels Click]

677
01:14:49,379 --> 01:14:51,370
This way!

678
01:14:55,285 --> 01:14:57,276
[Stachel]
The new monoplane!

679
01:14:59,956 --> 01:15:01,947
Is it as fast
as we've heard?

680
01:15:02,025 --> 01:15:04,459
Faster!

681
01:15:04,527 --> 01:15:06,791
What about
its maneuverability?

682
01:15:06,863 --> 01:15:09,593
Only one wing...
will it take the stress?

683
01:15:09,666 --> 01:15:13,898
It will out-turn any Allied plane
present in the air!

684
01:15:13,970 --> 01:15:17,303
It could even turn the tide
of the air war!

685
01:15:17,373 --> 01:15:20,467
Then we must have it!

686
01:15:20,543 --> 01:15:23,808
What would your reaction be if I told you
that these gentlemen believe!!!

687
01:15:23,880 --> 01:15:28,579
That there will be risks for you pilots
if we hurry it into production now?

688
01:15:30,086 --> 01:15:32,418
Well, we're used to risks,
Herr General.

689
01:15:32,488 --> 01:15:34,615
One more wouldn't
make any difference!

690
01:15:34,691 --> 01:15:38,286
- Hmm!
- Leutnant Stachel!

691
01:15:42,031 --> 01:15:44,056
- [Boot Heels Click]
- Tell me!

692
01:15:44,133 --> 01:15:47,660
Do you think that your opinion would
be shared by your comrades?

693
01:15:47,737 --> 01:15:49,728
I am certain of it,
Herr Field Marshal!

694
01:15:54,711 --> 01:15:59,080
- Let me see it again!
- [Wind Machine Starts]

695
01:16:06,289 --> 01:16:07,090
[Car Horn Honking]

696
01:16:07,090 --> 01:16:09,183
[Car Horn Honking]

697
01:16:39,188 --> 01:16:41,656
[Man Groaning]
Nurse!

698
01:16:44,027 --> 01:16:47,485
[Man] Nurse!
Nurse, come quickly.

699
01:16:47,563 --> 01:16:49,588
Come along,
Herr Leutnant.

700
01:16:52,668 --> 01:16:55,865
Frau Heidemann,
Leutnant Stachel!

701
01:16:55,938 --> 01:16:58,133
- [Boot Heels Click]
- Yes! I remember you!

702
01:16:58,207 --> 01:17:02,735
- I'm due back in a few minutes!
- It won't take long!

703
01:17:02,812 --> 01:17:05,940
The jacket, please, Herr Leutnant.
And your shirt!

704
01:17:14,590 --> 01:17:16,581
Frau Heidemann!
Those flowers, please!

705
01:17:19,128 --> 01:17:21,187
Thank you!

706
01:17:35,778 --> 01:17:37,769
Thank you!

707
01:17:37,847 --> 01:17:39,838
Sit down, Herr Leutnant.

708
01:17:50,626 --> 01:17:52,617
Excuse me, please!

709
01:17:55,264 --> 01:17:57,630
Mm-hmm!
Excellent!

710
01:17:57,700 --> 01:17:59,691
[Footsteps Leaving]

711
01:17:59,769 --> 01:18:02,237
I saw how busy
you were outside!

712
01:18:02,305 --> 01:18:04,296
- Yes!
- I'm sorry!

713
01:18:04,373 --> 01:18:06,364
[Holbach]
Come along, gentlemen.

714
01:18:06,442 --> 01:18:09,240
Along here!

715
01:18:09,312 --> 01:18:11,507
Now, Frau Heidemann,
if you please!!!

716
01:18:11,581 --> 01:18:13,981
It is just
this one pose, hmm?

717
01:18:15,852 --> 01:18:18,252
What are you going
to put under the picture?

718
01:18:18,321 --> 01:18:22,451
- "Squadron commander's wife
nurses wounded hero"?
- Yes!

719
01:18:22,525 --> 01:18:24,516
Please!

720
01:18:28,664 --> 01:18:30,655
Oh, very good!

721
01:18:30,733 --> 01:18:34,829
[Holbach]
Now move a little closer.

722
01:18:34,904 --> 01:18:39,034
Thank you!
Now!!! Hold still!

723
01:18:48,117 --> 01:18:50,483
[Chattering]

724
01:18:51,888 --> 01:18:53,981
- The playacting is over?
- Yes, Herr General.

725
01:18:54,056 --> 01:18:56,047
We have finished!

726
01:18:56,125 --> 01:18:58,116
Elfi, my dear!

727
01:18:58,194 --> 01:19:01,391
How good of you to have found time
to come and help us!

728
01:19:01,464 --> 01:19:03,762
It was an order, Herr General,
wasn't it?

729
01:19:03,833 --> 01:19:05,858
Of course!

730
01:19:05,935 --> 01:19:09,427
It was a very important
piece of playacting!

731
01:19:09,505 --> 01:19:11,496
I see!

732
01:19:23,619 --> 01:19:27,612
Well, Stachel, by morning,
you'll be quite famous!

733
01:19:27,690 --> 01:19:29,681
How do you feel
about that?

734
01:19:31,694 --> 01:19:35,790
- Lucky, Herr General.
- Hmm.

735
01:19:35,865 --> 01:19:40,802
- Tomorrow, you will be making
your way back to your squadron!
- [Boot Heels Click]

736
01:19:42,505 --> 01:19:46,635
And tonight, my wife
would like you to dine with her!

737
01:19:49,245 --> 01:19:52,840
That's!!! Very kind of her,
Herr General.

738
01:19:52,915 --> 01:19:56,009
Not at all!
She likes heroes!

739
01:19:57,086 --> 01:19:59,077
8:00!

740
01:20:00,056 --> 01:20:02,047
[Door Closes]

741
01:20:06,829 --> 01:20:07,830
¶¶[Piano, Softly]

742
01:20:07,830 --> 01:20:09,991
¶¶[Piano, Softly]

743
01:20:14,303 --> 01:20:16,237
You don't convince me
for one moment, Colonel!

744
01:20:16,305 --> 01:20:19,638
Herr Leutnant, may I ask you, please,
do you envy the birds?

745
01:20:19,709 --> 01:20:21,734
It may surprise you,
General, to know!!!

746
01:20:21,811 --> 01:20:24,177
Is that what makes men
want to fly...

747
01:20:24,247 --> 01:20:27,239
- jealousy of the birds?
- That I'm a serious student
of military strategy!

748
01:20:27,316 --> 01:20:29,477
No, Baroness, I am not
